ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection

Class ImmutableHugeArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.AbstractHugeArrayList<E>
          • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.ImmutableHugeArrayList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class ImmutableHugeArrayList<E>
extends AbstractHugeArrayList<E>
    An immutable List that stores elements in a MemoryManager.

    The mutating operations throw UnsupportedOperationException:

    • AbstractList.set(int, Object)
    • AbstractList.add(Object)
    • AbstractList.add(int, Object)
    • AbstractCollection.addAll(Collection)
    • AbstractList.addAll(int, Collection)
    • AbstractList.remove(int)
    • AbstractCollection.remove(Object)
    • AbstractCollection.removeAll(Collection)
    • AbstractList.clear()
    • Iterator.remove() when iterating over this collection

    In order to create an ImmutableHugeArrayList you must add the elements in the ImmutableHugeArrayList.Builder.

    Other than the mutating operations all semantics, memory consumption and performance are identical to HugeArrayList.

    See Also:
    HugeArrayList
